This paper is about developing a strong playing program for the game 2048 using reinforcement learning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also discusses various methods for improving the learning process, such as multi-stage function approximators and redundant encoding, which are common topics in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also mentions the use of Markov decision processes, which falls under the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The paper also discusses the use of parallelism, which is a topic in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of temporal difference learning, which is a common topic in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
